mrmc.core

Class InputFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • mrmc.core.InputFile

  • public class InputFile
extends java.lang.Object
    Handles input of a raw study data file
    • getReaderIDs, getNreader,
    • getNormalIDs, getNnormal,
    • getDiseaseIDs, getNdisease,
    • getModalityIDs, getNmodality,
    • ----KEY FIELDS----
    • keyedData, truthVals
    • These are not private and are accessed directly, like a structure. Do not modify.
    CALLED FROM: GUInterface.brwsButtonListener and SimRoeMetz
    Author:
    Xin He, Ph.D,, Brandon D. Gallas, Ph.D, Rohan Pathare

      • generateROCpoints

        public java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,java.util.TreeSet<XYPair>> generateROCpoints(java.lang.String mod)
        For a given modality, determines XY coordinates of ROC points for each reader of the study. Moves threshold from minimum to maximum score and calculates false positive fraction and true positive fraction at each sample.
        Parameters:
        mod - Modality for which ROC curves are being determined
        Returns:
        TreeMap where the key identifies a reader and the corresponding value is a set of XY coordinates of ROC points

      • generatePooledROC

        public java.util.TreeSet<XYPair> generatePooledROC(java.lang.String rocMod)
        For a given modality, determines XY coordinates of ROC points for pooled scores of all readers as one group. Moves threshold from minimum to maximum score and calculates false positive fraction and true positive fraction at each sample.
        Parameters:
        rocMod - Modality for which ROC curve is being determined
        Returns:
        Set of XY coordinates of ROC points

      • organizeData

        private void organizeData(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> fileContent)
                   throws java.io.IOException
        Reads the input file.
        ----Takes lines from .imrmc file and gets experiment information from header.
        ----Determines the readerIDs, normalIDs, diseaseIDs and modalityIDs.
        ----Compares experiment information in header to that found in the data.
        ----Creates caseIDs by concatenating normalIDs and diseaseIDs
        ----Creates the core data structures keyedData and truthVals.
        Parameters:
        fileContent - ArrayList of Strings of each line from file
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        See Also:
        recordTitle, verificationDetails, processScoresAndTruth(String[][])

      • processScoresAndTruth

        private void processScoresAndTruth(java.lang.String[][] fData)
                            throws java.io.IOException
        Creates the core data structures keyedData and truthVals.
        Creates caseIDs that are ordered with the normal cases first, followed by the disease cases
        The structure is (readerIDs(caseIDs(modalityIDs, score)))
        Checks for duplicate observations
        Parameters:
        fData - Individual scores with reader, case information
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        See Also:
        readerIDs, normalIDs, diseaseIDs, caseIDs, modalityIDs

      • verifySizesAndGetIDs

        private java.lang.String verifySizesAndGetIDs(java.lang.String[][] fData)
                                       throws java.io.IOException
        Determines the IDs of all the readers, cases, and modalities.
        ----Determines truth status of cases
        ----Checks for duplicate cases
        ----Checks that cases have truth
        ----Compares the number of modalities in the data to that specified in the header
        ----Sets Nreader to the number of disease cases in the data
        Parameters:
        fData - 2-D array where first dimension is line number from file, second dimension is reader, case, modality, score information
        Returns:
        String describing inconsistencies between header info and actual study info
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        See Also:
        readerIDs, normalIDs, diseaseIDs, modalityIDs
